\begin_layout Subsection
Continuous
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The continuous aspect is the unmarked aspect; it denotes an observation
 or prediction that a certain event is in progress.
 When a verb conjugation does not contain an aspect morpheme, then the continuou
s aspect is meant.
 For example, 
\series bold
kérista
\series default
 
\emph on
is loving
\emph default
, from the stem 
\series bold
kéri-
\series default
 and the tense suffix 
\series bold
-sta
\series default
 denoting present tense, is in the continuous aspect due to the lack of
 an aspect marker.
\end_layout

